## Parte 5 -  Configure VLANs, Trunks and Access Ports (Switch) - depende das portas físicas

###Switch(SW1-St)

#### a. Criar Vlan

enable
configure terminal
vlan 5
 name APs
vlan 6
 name MANAGEMENT
vlan 7
 name NATIVE
vlan 10
 name SERVERS
vlan 20
 name ADMINISTRATION
vlan 30
 name STAFF
vlan 40
 name VOIP
vlan 50
 name WIRELESS
vlan 60
 name GUESTS
vlan 99
 name BLACKHOLE
exit

#### b. Configurar trunks e portas de acesso
-RT1-St
interface FastEthernet0/1
 switchport mode trunk
 switchport trunk native vlan 7
 switchport trunk allowed vlan 5,6,30,50,60
 switchport nonegotiate
 no shutdown
exit

- PCD
interface range FastEthernet0/2 - 15
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 30
 switchport nonegotiate
exit

- Ap1-St
interface FastEthernet0/21
 switchport mode trunk
 switchport trunk native vlan 5
 switchport trunk allowed vlan 5,50,60
 switchport nonegotiate
 no shutdown
exit
interface FastEthernet0/22
 switchport mode trunk
 switchport trunk native vlan 5
 switchport trunk allowed vlan 5,50,60
 switchport nonegotiate
 no shutdown
exit

- Portas não usadas - Vlan 99(blackhole) e shutdown
interface range FastEthernet0/16 - 20
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 99
 switchport nonegotiate
 shutdown
exit

interface FastEthernet0/23
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 99
 switchport nonegotiate
 shutdown
exit
interface FastEthernet0/24
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 99
 switchport nonegotiate
